You are a senior frontend engineer. Build a single-page Enterprise SaaS landing page for “NatureX Service Hub”, matching the provided screenshots’ structure and tone.

Tech stack:
- Next.js (App Router) + React + TypeScript
- TailwindCSS
- shadcn/ui components
- lucide-react icons

Deliverable:
- Provide complete code for one page: `app/(marketing)/page.tsx` (or `app/page.tsx`)
- Include any small helper components inside the same file (or clearly split into components if needed)
- Must be responsive (desktop-first, then tablet/mobile)
- Use clean, minimal enterprise UI like NAVER WORKS style.

Brand / Copy:
- Top-left logo text: “NatureX”
- Small tagline near logo: “explore nature’s X with InvaLab”
- Main hero headline (centered): “Where nature’s X is discovered”
- Hero subheadline: “We explore nature to uncover its hidden value.”
- Section title: “NatureX Service Hub”

Global UI controls (top right):
- Language toggle pill: KR / EN
- Theme toggle icon (sun/moon)
- Keep these functional: toggling should switch visible copy KR/EN; theme toggle can be a simple state-driven style switch (light/dark) if you don’t want full next-themes.

Color system (light mode):
- Page background: #F5F7FB
- Card background: #FFFFFF
- Primary button: #118DFF
- Primary hover: slightly darker (#0F7FE6)
- Text:
  - title: #111827
  - body: #374151
  - muted: #6B7280
- Border: #E5E7EB
- Subtle shadow for cards

Layout sections (single continuous page):
1) Top nav (sticky optional):
